{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592574","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592574"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:16:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:16:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15263"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15263","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15263"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.32,0.13,0,0.52,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7954"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65977"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7954","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7954"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15263"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51426"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7662"},{"type":"tags","id":"7674"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19362"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19365"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22054"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65977","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65977"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EIntestinal-type gastric adenocarcinoma is one of the main histological subtypes of gastric cancer.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes this type of tumour?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Demonstrates E-cadherin loss","Develops without precursor lesions","Predominantly affects young adults","Primarily affects people aged 60 years and older","Shows equal gender distribution"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIntestinal-type gastric adenocarcinoma has distinct epidemiological and pathological features. \u003Cstrong\u003EPrimarily affecting people aged 60 years and older\u003C/strong\u003E, it shows a male predominance (2:1 male to female ratio), not a \u003Cstrong\u003Eequal gender distribution\u003C/strong\u003E. The tumour develops through a well-defined sequence of precursor lesions (Correa cascade), rather than \u003Cstrong\u003Edeveloping without precursor lesions\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EE-cadherin loss\u003C/strong\u003E is characteristic of diffuse-type gastric cancer, not intestinal-type. This cancer rarely \u003Cstrong\u003Epredominantly affects young adults\u003C/strong\u003E, with most cases occurring in older populations with chronic gastritis and intestinal metaplasia.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe development typically follows environmental risk factors including \u003Cem\u003EHelicobacter pylori\u003C/em\u003E infection, dietary factors, and smoking.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Intestinal-type gastric adenocarcinoma typically affects older adults (\u003E60 years) with a male predominance.","Intestinal-type gastric cancer develops through a sequence of precursor lesions including atrophic gastritis and intestinal metaplasia.","Loss of E-cadherin is characteristic of diffuse-type, not intestinal-type, gastric cancer."],"references":["Ajani JA, Lee J, Sano T, Janjigian YY, Fan D, Song S. Gastric adenocarcinoma. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2017 Jun 1;3:17036. doi: 10.1038/nrdp.2017.36. PMID: 28569272","Menon G, El-Nakeep S, Babiker HM. Gastric Cancer. [Updated 2024 Oct 28]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://ww